      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) < 5% for hemolysis index QoI across at least three systematically refined meshes at all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "GCI study performed using three mesh levels (4.2M, 8.7M, 17.1M cells). GCI values ranged from 3.8% to 7.4% across the five operating points; two high-flow conditions exceeded the 5% threshold. The team judged overall discretization error acceptable given the relative hemolysis comparison framework, and the decision record reflects Accepted status. However, the achieved level of 2 falls below the required level of 3 for MRL 2 at High decision consequence, representing a shortfall that was not formally mitigated."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
